1. *Nazovite* me kada stignete kući. (Call me when you get home.)
2. Mogli biste *nazvati* restoran i rezervirati stol za večeru. (You could call the restaurant and make a dinner reservation.)
3. Nisam mogao *da nazovem* svoju sestru jer mi je baterija na telefonu bila prazna. (I couldn't call my sister because my phone battery was dead.)
4. Kada *bi me nazvao*, rekao bih mu sve što mislim. (If he called me, I would tell him everything I think.)
5. Nemoj *da me zoveš* tako kasno uveče, molim te. (Please don't call me so late in the evening.)
6. Prošlo je već pet dana, a on još nije *nazvao*. (It's been five days already, and he still hasn't called.)
7. *Nazvao bih* te da ti kažem dobre vijesti. (I would call you to tell you the good news.)
8. Pozvao sam je nekoliko puta, ali ona me nije *nazvala* natrag. (I called her several times, but she didn't call me back.)
9. Ne mogu *da nazovem* poštu jer mi ne radi telefon. (I can't call the post office because my phone isn't working.)
10. Molim vas da *nazovete* policiju ako primijetite bilo kakvu sumnjivu aktivnost. (Please call the police if you notice any suspicious activity.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "nazovite" is the imperative form of the verb "nazvati" which means "to call" in English. It can also appear in different verb tenses such as past, conditional, and infinitive.